New Records: Morocco defeated Congo Brazzaville 6-0 in the World Cup African Qualifiers, with goals scored by Azeddine Ounahi (8′), Chadi Ryad (16′), Ayoub El Kaabi (20′, 39′, 53′), and Soufiane Rahimi (62′). This victory moved Morocco to the top of Pool E with 9 points.
Morocco leads Pool E with 9 points after their 6-0 win against Congo Brazzaville, having previously earned 6 points from draws against Tanzania (0-2) and Zambia (2-1).
Key Match Events: Morocco secured a 6-0 victory over Congo Brazzaville in their World Cup African Qualifier match.
Tanzania also secured a 1-0 win against Zambia in the same group, moving to second place behind Morocco.
